block content

  +state('Georgia', '/assets/images/flag-georgia.svg', 'The Peach State', 'January 2, 1788')

  .intro
    p Georgia holds a few flag records. Not only has it had the most flags (eight different iterations), its current flag is the most recently adopted of the entire nation’s.
    p The flag has created controversy for the state. The 1956 version featured the Confederate battle flag, adopted soon after Brown v. Board of Education ruled segregation unconstitutional.
    p The current flag, based on the first Confederate national flag (“Stars and Bars”) was officially adopted May 8, 2003.
    p The people of Georgia voted to keep this version of the flag in a referendum on March 2, 2004.

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Flag design
      p The Georgia flag features three horizontal bars of red, white, and red. In the upper left corner is a square canton of blue on which a ring of 13 white stars is placed, surrounding the state’s coat of arms in gold. Below the coat of arms, the words “In God We Trust” are inscribed.
    .visual.flag
      img(src='/assets/images/flag-georgia.svg')

  .guide.wide
    .content
      h2 Iconography
      ul.visual.icon-list
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-georgia-icon-stars.svg')
          h4 13 stars
          p The circle of thirteen stars represents the original thirteen colonies, of which Georgia was included.
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-georgia-icon-pillars.svg')
          h4 3 pillars
          p Each pillar represents a branch of government: executive, legislative, and judicial.
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-georgia-icon-militia.svg')
          h4 Militia
          p While the pillars support the Constitution, a member of the Georgia militia stands guard.
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-georgia-icon-in-god-we-trust.svg')
          h4 In God We Trust
          p These words, not seen in the coat of arms or state seal, serve as a foundation for all above it.

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Coat of Arms
      p The original coat of arms featured the date 1799 (as seen to the right). In 1914, the date was changed to 1776 to reference the signing of the Declaration of Independence.
      p Featured on the scrolls are the words of the state motto “Wisdom, Justice, and Moderation.”
    .visual.flag
      img(src='/assets/images/coat-of-arms-georgia.jpg')

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Colors
      p Colors include blue, red, white, and gold. The blue and red match the United States flag.
